1
00:00:18,875 --> 00:00:22,833
[MOURNER WALLA]

2
00:00:22,916 --> 00:00:26,375
A tragedy such as this
must never happen again.

3
00:00:26,458 --> 00:00:29,875
Those we lost and the pain
they have left behind.

4
00:00:29,958 --> 00:00:32,375
Should not be suffered in vain.

5
00:00:32,458 --> 00:00:34,708
We can never be
allowed to forget.

6
00:00:34,791 --> 00:00:39,916
Mom... Ai... Dad...

7
00:00:41,083 --> 00:00:44,791
[FAMILY WALLA]

8
00:00:45,625 --> 00:00:48,916
I can't believe all
this is my dad's fault.

9
00:00:51,125 --> 00:00:53,083
[church bells ringing]

10
00:00:57,750 --> 00:00:59,041
What's this?

11
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:00,750
It's wet.

12
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:02,791
Why would this be
happening to me?

13
00:01:13,291 --> 00:01:15,250
I don't understand.

14
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:55,791
Otohime?

15
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:01,166
What is it?

16
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:03,208
[dragon roars]

17
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:08,625
Target confirmed
as an unknown dragon.

18
00:03:08,708 --> 00:03:11,791
It's the Neo-Original
that attacked L-3 Base.

19
00:03:11,875 --> 00:03:14,291
It traveled from Lagrange-3

20
00:03:14,375 --> 00:03:18,916
to the Earth's surface
in only 267 seconds.

21
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,583
I have the target in sight.

22
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:22,750
I'm moving in.

23
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:30,875
It's huge.

24
00:03:33,083 --> 00:03:33,958
[dragon growls]

25
00:03:34,041 --> 00:03:35,875
Careful, Howlingstar.

26
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:48,375
[SIEGLINDE gasps]

27
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:51,625
Where'd it go?
I don't see it.

28
00:03:54,916 --> 00:03:56,666
It's gone.

29
00:03:57,541 --> 00:03:59,416
What the hell is that thing?

30
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:21,541
Where am I?

31
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:25,083
What is all this?

32
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,416
There will be
a hearing regarding

33
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,416
the Album incident later.

34
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,250
Stay there and
keep an eye

35
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:35,708
on Gio and Widow until you
receive further instructions.

36
00:04:35,791 --> 00:04:38,541
I'm concerned those
two might start rampaging.

37
00:04:38,625 --> 00:04:40,583
Watch them here?

38
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,708
But what about the Album.

39
00:04:42,791 --> 00:04:44,458
We have to get the Album back!

40
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:46,416
Listen Kitajima, once more,

41
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:49,458
there's no need for
you to come back here.

42
00:04:49,541 --> 00:04:52,000
Think of it as house arrest.

43
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,916
Wait there for instructions.

44
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,291
Please wait, Professor!

45
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:57,833
I don't think you see.

46
00:04:58,541 --> 00:05:01,166
You don't see
you're much safer there.

47
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:04,041
Both you and the Dragons.

48
00:05:14,125 --> 00:05:15,416
Hey!

49
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,375
Let me out of here!

50
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:20,041
I've got to help Toa!

51
00:05:22,166 --> 00:05:24,166
[GIO growling]

52
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:26,958
It won't work.

53
00:05:29,666 --> 00:05:31,875
That room is covered by CSS.

54
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:34,958
It's impossible
for you to actualize.

55
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:38,041
What are you
going to do with us?

56
00:05:38,125 --> 00:05:39,750
Don't worry about it.

57
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:41,250
Behave yourselves.

58
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:43,916
And everything will be alright.

59
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:47,666
You want us to behave
ourselves do you?

60
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:00,416
In this state,
nothing would happen

61
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:03,166
if they did start rampaging.

62
00:06:08,125 --> 00:06:10,041
It's strange.

63
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:13,666
Neither one of them is
showing signs of losing control.

64
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:16,125
Why would the professor
say what he did?

65
00:06:19,916 --> 00:06:22,291
It's like he's hiding
something from me.

66
00:06:24,625 --> 00:06:28,708
From now on we will refer
to the Neo-Original as Ostrum.

67
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:31,583
The D project
stands on the precipice

68
00:06:31,666 --> 00:06:34,875
of phase 7 and
then this happens.

69
00:06:34,958 --> 00:06:38,333
Ostrum destroyed L-3 Base,

70
00:06:38,416 --> 00:06:40,458
It brought down Otohime.

71
00:06:40,541 --> 00:06:43,708
Unlike the Album, it is
clearly a hostile force.

72
00:06:43,791 --> 00:06:45,416
Why did it disappear?

73
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:48,541
Professor Nozaki do you
know what its objective is?

74
00:06:48,625 --> 00:06:51,000
It didn't disappear.

75
00:06:51,083 --> 00:06:52,750
Look at this.

76
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:56,500
This is the moment
Ostrum vanished.

77
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,708
Right here.

78
00:06:58,791 --> 00:07:01,708
At the same moment, a spatial
distortion appears.

79
00:07:01,791 --> 00:07:05,083
I believe a large body
moved into alternate space.

80
00:07:05,166 --> 00:07:08,000
It's possible.

81
00:07:08,083 --> 00:07:11,000
We just saw Ostrum
become a Communicator.

82
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:12,666
What?

83
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:13,500
It can't be!

84
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,000
That's not possible.

85
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:17,416
When could it have gone through
a resonance and with whom?

86
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,166
I don't know the reason why.

87
00:07:19,250 --> 00:07:22,250
However, if the case
of the Album and Jin

88
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:23,666
can shed any light.

89
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:25,416
We should fully
expect that this original

90
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:28,666
won't be bound by
the orders of any master.

91
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:31,416
An unrestricted Dragon
has taken human form.

92
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:35,708
You'd be right to call
this a worst-case scenario.

93
00:07:35,791 --> 00:07:37,208
In my opinion?

94
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:40,000
We should begin
evacuating this entire city.

95
00:07:40,083 --> 00:07:41,333
No way!

96
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:43,375
Do you know how many
people we're talking about?

97
00:07:43,458 --> 00:07:46,041
Evacuate the entire island
and remove all the people

98
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:48,041
we are not looking for,
is that your plan?

99
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:50,375
Yes.

100
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:53,500
Whatever remains is the enemy.

101
00:07:56,625 --> 00:07:58,291
[ANNOUNCER]
This is ISDA Security.

102
00:07:58,375 --> 00:08:01,375
An evacuation order has been
issued for the entire island.

103
00:08:01,458 --> 00:08:03,916
Please proceed to the
nearest evacuation center

104
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,708
with your resident ID.

105
00:08:05,791 --> 00:08:08,000
After processing,
you will be allowed to board

106
00:08:08,083 --> 00:08:10,500
your designated
ship or aircraft.

107
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:12,000
This is just absurd.

108
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:15,041
Where are we supposed
to be looking?

109
00:08:15,125 --> 00:08:17,416
What happens if he stays hidden?

110
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:20,166
I guess they'll
have us go door to door.

111
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,708
They might, but waiting
for him to use his powers

112
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:25,416
is not an option we
want to face right now.

113
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:27,375
I know that, I'm just saying.

114
00:08:27,458 --> 00:08:30,291
Kazuki, you're in charge
of coordinating the evacuation.

115
00:08:30,375 --> 00:08:32,916
Work in conjunction
with the special forces unit.

116
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,958
Got it?

117
00:08:35,041 --> 00:08:37,166
Roger.

118
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:44,500
Why... why am I forced
to be just a traffic cop?

119
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:46,458
Why?

120
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,458
Nothing.

121
00:08:55,541 --> 00:08:57,458
I don't hear anything.

122
00:08:57,541 --> 00:09:00,125
It's like my sense
of Toa has disappeared.

123
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:03,791
So then, she's gone someplace
else for a little while?

124
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:06,916
I don't know.

125
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,250
Listen--

126
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:12,208
I'm sure that Toa is
trying to accomplish something.

127
00:09:12,291 --> 00:09:13,750
And it must be important.

128
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:16,333
I just don't know what it is.

129
00:09:16,416 --> 00:09:18,041
First she lets
herself get caught

130
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:20,958
and then she turns around
and runs off somewhere else.

131
00:09:21,041 --> 00:09:24,125
It doesn't make
much sense, does it?

132
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:25,958
I don't know
anything about Toa.

133
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:29,333
She never told me
about herself.

134
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,875
I'll find her.

135
00:09:31,958 --> 00:09:34,458
That's the only way
I'll ever know.

136
00:09:34,541 --> 00:09:36,333
Akira!

137
00:09:36,416 --> 00:09:38,666
A fourth Original
Dragon has appeared.

138
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:40,541
What'd you say?

139
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:42,250
Original?

140
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,875
You mean like Toa?

141
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:45,750
[ANNOUNCER] This is
the ISDA Security.

142
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:49,833
An evacuation order has been
issued for the entire island.

143
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:52,666
[SECURITY A] This
is search team 21,

144
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:55,458
currently located in
underground corridor E-46.

145
00:09:55,541 --> 00:10:00,375
Commander,
everything appears to be clear.

146
00:10:01,083 --> 00:10:02,125
[SECURITY A] Wait.

147
00:10:02,208 --> 00:10:03,833
Possible subject sighted.

148
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:07,708
[SECURITY B] You there,
what are you doing down here?

149
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:09,958
[SECURITY A] We're
approaching the suspect now.

150
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:11,208
[SECURITY B] Why didn't you
go to your evacuation center?

151
00:10:11,291 --> 00:10:13,291
I need to see
your identification.

152
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:16,375
[SECURITY B] Sir!

153
00:10:16,458 --> 00:10:18,250
[OSTRUM growls]

154
00:10:19,666 --> 00:10:23,500
We're picking up a pulse
from Sector 6 of Shin City!

155
00:10:23,583 --> 00:10:24,875
It's the Ostrum sir.

156
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:26,833
Send in Cromwell and Baumgard.

157
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:28,708
We've got fires
in the area sir.

158
00:10:28,791 --> 00:10:30,458
[MEGUMI] I've got
the target on screen.

159
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:32,958
[MEGUMI] It's headed straight
for evacuation center Alpha 9.

160
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:34,458
That's a bus transit hub.

161
00:10:34,541 --> 00:10:37,500
They're still loading
people to the airport.

162
00:10:37,583 --> 00:10:39,541
Howlingstar!
Get us there, now.

163
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:49,041
This just sucks.

164
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:52,125
I can't stand anymore.

165
00:10:53,041 --> 00:10:58,000
Of course, if you succeed,
well, then, no harm done.

166
00:10:58,083 --> 00:11:01,333
I get it.

167
00:11:05,916 --> 00:11:07,791
Gio is mine.

168
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:12,583
Please board the buses
in an orderly manner.

169
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:15,083
We'll be at the airport soon.

170
00:11:15,166 --> 00:11:16,208
[EVACUEE WALLA]

171
00:11:41,083 --> 00:11:43,291
Dragon!

172
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:50,375
You desire to get rid of us.

173
00:11:50,958 --> 00:11:53,375
Well then.

174
00:11:57,708 --> 00:12:00,291
There's been an
explosion in Sector 7!

175
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:02,958
It's on screen now.

176
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:07,208
What is it?

177
00:12:27,166 --> 00:12:29,791
What's going on over there?

178
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:32,041
This doesn't look good.

179
00:12:37,541 --> 00:12:40,666
We didn't make it in time.

180
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,708
Sieglinde, here he comes!

181
00:12:42,791 --> 00:12:43,708
I see him.

182
00:12:43,791 --> 00:12:45,000
He's mine.

183
00:12:45,083 --> 00:12:46,750
Wait!

184
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:48,333
Here it goes!

185
00:12:54,416 --> 00:12:56,375
[SIEGLINDE yelps in pain]

186
00:13:05,166 --> 00:13:06,833
He's fast.

187
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,708
That's gotta be
the fourth Original dragon.

188
00:13:12,791 --> 00:13:15,500
I bet he's responsible
for that explosion.

189
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:33,958
Akira.

190
00:13:34,041 --> 00:13:37,375
You always know
what I'm thinking.

191
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:38,958
[AKIRA sighs]

192
00:13:39,041 --> 00:13:43,375
It's so hard to watch what's
happening and do nothing.

193
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:47,833
I'm not even a Dragonaut
anymore but I can't sit here.

194
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:49,666
Yeah I know.

195
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:51,375
It's time to go.

196
00:13:51,458 --> 00:13:52,750
Are you ready, Machina?

197
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:54,958
Yes, Akira.

198
00:13:55,041 --> 00:13:56,833
Akira!

199
00:13:56,916 --> 00:14:01,625
I... just want to thank
you for everything.

200
00:14:01,708 --> 00:14:04,500
Sure.

201
00:14:05,291 --> 00:14:06,500
Jin,

202
00:14:06,583 --> 00:14:09,208
You make sure to find
Toa now, all right?

203
00:14:09,291 --> 00:14:11,916
Gio is being
isolated on Tartarus.

204
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,166
Go to him, quickly.

205
00:14:27,625 --> 00:14:28,708
Machina.

206
00:14:28,791 --> 00:14:30,375
Let's do this!

207
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:35,500
You!

208
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,875
[YONAMINE]
Hey, I can give you a lift.

209
00:14:37,958 --> 00:14:39,916
If you're interested.

210
00:14:49,291 --> 00:14:51,166
I've got you now.

211
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:56,000
No way!

212
00:14:56,958 --> 00:14:59,583
His heat is melting the ground.

213
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:05,250
Sieglinde!

214
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:06,625
[MACHINA roars]

215
00:15:06,708 --> 00:15:08,291
What?

216
00:15:11,583 --> 00:15:13,833
It's... water.

217
00:15:13,916 --> 00:15:16,291
From who?

218
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:17,750
[MACHINA roars]

219
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:19,916
Machina!

220
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,375
Here goes!

221
00:15:26,708 --> 00:15:30,208
See that!

222
00:15:30,291 --> 00:15:32,375
He can't take a little rain.

223
00:15:32,458 --> 00:15:35,541
I hope you didn't
just cool him off.

224
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:37,458
Why did you decide to show up?

225
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:38,875
What's your problem?

226
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:40,000
I just saved you.

227
00:15:40,083 --> 00:15:41,750
I had everything under control.

228
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:43,666
You're such a little princess!

229
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:53,375
Dork.

230
00:15:53,458 --> 00:15:54,666
Okay.

231
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:57,166
Do you wanna tell me
who you really are?

232
00:15:57,250 --> 00:15:58,375
[YONAMINE] What?

233
00:15:58,458 --> 00:15:59,875
I'm just a reporter.

234
00:15:59,958 --> 00:16:01,416
Yeah right.

235
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:04,666
Then why do you
keep helping me out?

236
00:16:05,750 --> 00:16:08,583
[YONAMINE] It's kind of
a favor for good friend of mine.

237
00:16:17,583 --> 00:16:20,250
Was that...?

238
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:22,458
[YONAMINE]
Hey, don't be in such a rush.

239
00:16:22,541 --> 00:16:24,458
You might get hurt.

240
00:16:42,458 --> 00:16:43,375
Gio!

241
00:16:43,458 --> 00:16:44,583
[JIN grunts in pain]

242
00:16:44,666 --> 00:16:46,250
Jin!

243
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:48,541
You're never going to take Gio!

244
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:50,791
Gio belongs to me!

245
00:16:50,875 --> 00:16:52,750
I created him!

246
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:54,208
You're wrong.

247
00:16:54,291 --> 00:16:56,500
He can't be owned.

248
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:02,375
Jin!

249
00:17:02,458 --> 00:17:04,083
No!

250
00:17:04,166 --> 00:17:05,958
Gio!

251
00:17:06,458 --> 00:17:08,250
Gio!
[KAZUKI grimaces in pain]

252
00:17:15,208 --> 00:17:16,375
Gio!

253
00:17:16,458 --> 00:17:17,791
Are you all right?

254
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:19,333
Listen, Jin.

255
00:17:19,416 --> 00:17:20,958
Toa's gone.

256
00:17:21,041 --> 00:17:23,208
She was taken away
by the Gillard Army.

257
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:24,416
Where'd they go?

258
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:28,291
[alarm beeping]

259
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:30,166
All right, Jin.

260
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:31,833
I'm done.

261
00:17:31,916 --> 00:17:34,416
No matter what I do,
you and Gio

262
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:37,583
will always try
to gang up on me.

263
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:40,583
In that case.

264
00:17:40,666 --> 00:17:42,625
I'll see you in hell!

265
00:17:47,583 --> 00:17:49,375
No Jin!

266
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,958
We can't stop him!

267
00:18:03,458 --> 00:18:05,583
Hang on!

268
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:10,666
We've lost communication.

269
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:12,166
The Lindworm unit
is totally black.

270
00:18:12,250 --> 00:18:14,000
Here he comes.

271
00:18:16,708 --> 00:18:19,833
[MEGUMI]
Ostrum is directly overhead!

272
00:18:19,916 --> 00:18:21,750
[MEGUMI] What should
we do now, Commander?

273
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:25,666
Our only option is move
the Avenir Timetable forward.

274
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:28,166
We must begin
Phase 7 immediately.

275
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:30,041
But Commander,
the assembly process

276
00:18:30,125 --> 00:18:31,666
is only 32 percent complete.

277
00:18:31,750 --> 00:18:33,750
Do it now!

278
00:18:33,833 --> 00:18:35,583
Sir, acknowledged.

279
00:18:37,083 --> 00:18:41,791
Attention personnel,
the base has begun immediate

280
00:18:41,875 --> 00:18:43,750
initiation into Phase 7.

281
00:18:43,833 --> 00:18:45,083
Repeat, Phase 7
has been initiated.

282
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:46,333
The base is moving to Phase 7.

283
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:56,375
Damn you for this dragon.

284
00:18:56,458 --> 00:19:09,125
Damn you for this dragon.

285
00:19:09,208 --> 00:19:11,166
Professor!

286
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:12,958
So you've come, have you?

287
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:15,625
Why didn't you tell me
a fourth Original was here?

288
00:19:15,708 --> 00:19:19,125
You chose to leave me
completely in the dark.

289
00:19:19,208 --> 00:19:22,875
She's tired.We should let
her go to sleep for awhile.

290
00:19:22,958 --> 00:19:25,583
She's done a lot
of good work for us.

291
00:19:25,666 --> 00:19:27,333
She?

292
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:30,166
Are you talking about the Raum?

293
00:19:30,250 --> 00:19:33,708
It's not like you to act
that way about a sample.

294
00:19:33,791 --> 00:19:36,583
It's not like me, right.

295
00:19:36,666 --> 00:19:38,250
Professor, don't.

296
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:40,250
What are you doing?

297
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:43,083
Please stop!

298
00:19:43,166 --> 00:19:44,875
Why?

299
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:47,250
How could you?

300
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:50,000
She's gone.

301
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:52,208
Why must you take
everything from me?

302
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:55,958
The Album and now this.

303
00:19:56,041 --> 00:19:59,000
You shouldn't have
to rely on such things.

304
00:19:59,083 --> 00:20:02,708
Does it give you pleasure
to see me accomplish nothing?

305
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:05,458
I was convinced you knew it all.

306
00:20:05,541 --> 00:20:07,625
I've always looked up to you.

307
00:20:07,708 --> 00:20:10,000
Why did you change?

308
00:20:14,916 --> 00:20:18,125
Hey, what's wrong?

309
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,833
He's here.

310
00:20:31,875 --> 00:20:34,875
This is the last
chance for you, Gio.

311
00:20:34,958 --> 00:20:37,291
Let him go.

312
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,041
I see.

313
00:20:40,125 --> 00:20:43,125
You really prefer Jin that much?

314
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:44,708
Fine.

315
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:47,541
You'll die with him!

316
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:52,833
[KAZUKI laughing maniacally]

317
00:20:52,916 --> 00:20:54,416
Tell me, why are you
allied with the humans?

318
00:20:54,500 --> 00:21:01,833
Because that is
what I want.

319
00:21:01,916 --> 00:21:05,625
What you... want?

320
00:21:05,708 --> 00:21:09,625
[OSTRUM yelling]
What you want!

321
00:21:23,166 --> 00:21:25,166
What?

322
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:43,125
[GIO roars]

323
00:22:06,208 --> 00:22:07,416
Atrum.

324
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:10,875
It's here.

325
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:03,208
Up, up, down, L, R, B, A.

326
00:24:03,291 --> 00:24:04,833
Megumi, what are you doing?

327
00:24:04,916 --> 00:24:06,291
The all-powerful command.

328
00:24:06,375 --> 00:24:07,458
What's that?

329
00:24:07,541 --> 00:24:08,750
It gives you all weapons!

330
00:24:08,833 --> 00:24:10,541
I'll be able to
handle any enemy now.

331
00:24:10,625 --> 00:24:12,000
Even that huge Dragon!

332
00:24:12,083 --> 00:24:13,541
Uh-huh.

333
00:24:13,625 --> 00:24:15,833
It gives me the all-powerful
bombs and stuff!

334
00:24:15,916 --> 00:24:18,750
This is hopeless,
let's leave her alone.

335
00:24:18,833 --> 00:24:19,833
Yeah.

336
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:21,791
Next time, will
this finally be settled?

337
00:24:21,875 --> 00:24:24,708
Megumi, you're still on
the Level 1, aren't you?

